The paper presents a novel approach for representative selection from high-dimensional data that may exhibit non-linear structures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper's focus on maximizing the global representation power of the sampled subset, ensuring diversity, and rejecting disruptive information by effectively detecting outliers aligns with the research areas of these sub-categories.
